Manuel Rivas gana el Premio Nacional de: Manuel Rivas wins the 2024 National Prize for Literature.
El escritor gallego Manuel Rivas (A Coru: Galician writer Manuel Rivas (A Coruña, 67 years old) has been awarded the 2024 Spanish National Prize for Literature today, Tuesday. The jury highlighted the author for 'the extraordinary narrative quality that combines emotional strength and formal beauty, and for the solidity of a versatile and coherent career built with sensitivity and a commitment to historical memory, social responsibility, and the Galician language. Few authors in the Spanish literary scene, starting from a firm commitment to their language, have managed to achieve such worldwide recognition,' as stated in a communiqué from the Ministry of Culture, which grants the award. The prize, worth 50,000 euros, is awarded each year for 'the body of literary work of an author.
